OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FChance of a shower at first
OL,6,Facross Argyll, otherwise a dry morning
OL,7,Fwith some early brightness. Cloud in
OL,8,Fthe afternoon with occasional rain
OL,9,Fspreading north.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FCloudy with some outbreaks of
OL,12,Frain through the evening. Staying
OL,13,Fcloudy overnight with heavier bursts
OL,14,Fof rain developing at times. Strong
OL,15,Fsoutheast winds around the coast.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FCloudy as bands of rain
OL,18,Fpush northeast in the morning. Turning
OL,19,Fshowery later, these showers heavy and
OL,20,Fthundery at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
